  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 200°C and place English muffins on a baking sheet.",
    "Brush the cut sides of the muffins with olive oil and bake until lightly golden, about 5 minutes.",
    "Combine confit tomatoes, red wine vinegar, sea salt, black pepper, rosemary, thyme, smoked paprika, and lemon juice in a bowl; stir to mix.",
    "Spread the tomato mixture evenly over the toasted sides of the muffins.",
    "Return the muffins to the oven and bake for an additional 3 minutes until the tomatoes are warm and bubbly.",
    "Remove from oven, sprinkle toasted sesame seeds and chopped parsley over the top.",
    "Let the toast cool for 2 minutes before serving."
  ],
